Blackpool Council has a statutory responsibility (Section 47(1) of the NHS and Community Care Act 1990) to carry out assessment of need for clients with substance misuse problems and offer residential provision if appropriate.

Blackpool Council is seeking proposals for two separate lots from suitably qualified and experienced providers for the provision of residential detoxification services (18 years old and over) and residential rehabilitation services (18 years old and over).   

&bull;

Blackpool Council has invited and evaluated quotations from suitably qualified and experienced planning consultants to:

(i)	undertake a retail capacity study for Blackpool to establish current provision and future needs;  
(ii)	to advise on introducing a local retail threshold for retail impact assessment and if appropriate the level of such a threshold; 
(iii)	to undertake a commercial leisure facilities (Use Class D2) assessment for Blackpool to establish current provision and future need
